This paper discusses attacks and defenses related to website fingerprinting, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper involves statistical analysis and modeling, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of network protocols and traffic analysis, which could fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
